#Create ec2 instance with public IP using terraform - Success

#Install jenkins on ec2 instance 

Issue 1 : 
```
Package jenkins is not available, but is referred to by another package.
This may mean that the package is missing, has been obsoleted, or
is only available from another source

E: Package 'jenkins' has no installation candidate
Failed to enable unit: Unit file jenkins.service does not exist.
Failed to start jenkins.service: Unit jenkins.service not found.
2025-11-07 06:32:29,164 - cc_scripts_user.py[WARNING]: Failed to run module scripts_user (scripts in /var/lib/cloud/instance/scripts)
2025-11-07 06:32:29,165 - log_util.py[WARNING]: Running module scripts_user (<module 'cloudinit.config.cc_scripts_user' from '/usr/lib/python3/dist-packages/cloudinit/config/cc_scripts_user.py'>) failed
Cloud-init v. 25.2-0ubuntu1~22.04.1 finished at Fri, 07 Nov 2025 06:32:29 +0000. Datasource DataSourceEc2Local.  Up 55.39 seconds
```

Inference and fix : Jenkins is not available from the default Ubuntu repositories, which happens because Jenkins is distributed from its official repository, not Ubuntu’s

sudo apt install -y fontconfig openjdk-17-jre

# 2. Add the Jenkins repo key and source list
curl -fsSL https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian/jenkins.io-2023.key | sudo tee \
  /usr/share/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc > /dev/null

echo deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc] \
  https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian binary/ | sudo tee \
  /etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list > /dev/null

#Access jenkins using public IP of ec2 instance - Success
